# Kayfa Platform Analytics Dashboard

A multipage Streamlit dashboard answering 15 business questions about student
attendance, performance, engagement, and risk on the Kayfa learning platform.

## Overview

Raw data was exported from multiple sources (Excel attendance sheets, nested
JSON grade records, MongoDB collections) and reconciled into clean, joinable
tables. The dashboard surfaces 15 analyses, each with a recommended chart,
methodology, key metrics, and a written insight + recommendation.

## Data sources

- `courses` — course catalogue (modules stored as JSON strings, parsed)
- `groups` — class cohorts (self-reported size, NOT source of truth)
- `students` — single source of truth for student → group → course mapping
- `grades` — flattened per-assessment scores (quiz, assignment, practical, exam)
- `attendance` — 6 monthly Excel sheets, reconciled (column names + status
  encodings vary by sheet and were standardized to `attended` / `absent`)
- `concepts_performance` — per-concept mastery over time
- `engagement_events` — behavioral log (currently video_watch only — login
  frequency is not available and is called out as a limitation)
- `assignment_submissions` — submission timing, used to study procrastination

## Known data limitations

- Engagement data only contains `video_watch` events. Login frequency,
  forum activity, etc. are not present, so engagement metrics use
  video-watch time and event count as proxies.
- `groups.stated_num_students` is self-reported and diverges from the true
  roster by up to 30 students in some groups (see Q12).
- C007 has only 1 enrolled student — treated as a non-comparable outlier
  cohort in course-level comparisons (see Q3, Q13).

## The 15 questions

| # | Question | Chart type | Key finding |
|---|----------|-----------|-------------|
| 1 | Attendance rate per group vs platform average | Bar + reference line | G07-C005 is 15.8pts below average |
| 2 | Score distribution by assessment type | Boxplot | Quizzes most volatile (std=19.9) |
| 3 | Highest/lowest avg grade course | Bar + boxplot | C001 highest (73.2%), C005 lowest (59.7%) |
| 4 | Attendance vs grade correlation | Scatter + regression | r=0.42, p<0.001 |
| 5 | Engagement vs performance | Scatter + heatmap | Video time r=0.38 vs grade |
| 6 | Concept failure rates | Horizontal bar | Recursion (C002) at 83.4% failure |
| 7 | Weakest concept mastery over time | Line chart | Flat trend (slope ≈ +0.0014) |
| 8 | Late submissions vs score | Boxplot + scatter | Late submissions score 4.6pts lower |
| 9 | Attendance & engagement over term | Multi-line | Cohort-wide dip 2026-03-02 to 03-16 |
| 10 | Age bands vs outcomes | Grouped bar | Minimal variation across age groups |
| 11 | Student segmentation | PCA + KMeans | 4 segments; Segment 1 (n=64) is at-risk |
| 12 | True vs stated group sizes | Grouped bar | 86 students total discrepancy |
| 13 | Smallest viable group | Similarity heatmap | G10 (n=1) — no same-course merge partner |
| 14 | At-risk student ranking | Horizontal ranked bar | Top 10 dominated by G07 students |
| 15 | Group grade trends over time | Multi-line | All groups trending flat/down; G10 worst |

## Tech stack

- **Data processing**: Python, pandas, numpy, scipy
- **Database**: MongoDB Atlas
- **Clustering**: scikit-learn (KMeans, StandardScaler)
- **Dashboard**: Streamlit + Plotly Express

